The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Essar Steel net profit shines

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, April 13: Essar Steel has reported a massive jump in net profit at Rs 590.15 crore for the year ended March 31 compared with Rs 59.99 crore in the previous financial year.

 Total income grew by 65 per cent to Rs 6,121.27 crore from Rs 3,717.65 crore last fiscal, a company release said.

 During the fourth quarter ended March 31, the company?s net profit rose to Rs 272.78 crore from Rs 98.02 crore in the same quarter last fiscal. 

 The total income for the same period was Rs 1,926.64 crore compared with Rs 1,227.11 crore in the year-ago period.

 Essar Steel chairman Shashi Ruia said the results reflected the success in achieving topline growth and substantially improving profitability.

 Value-added products accounted for over 35 per cent of the sales volume against 20 per cent last year, having a positive impact on profitability. 

 Demand continues to be bullish and measures are being adopted to remain a low-cost producer in the country, he added.

 The company?s thrust on adding value and flexibility in its product mix continued.

 Its concentration on value addition and customisation helped increase revenues and market penetration. 

 HR Pickled and Oiled (HRPO) coils and painted plates were among the new products introduced during the year. 




